snippet.textDisplay: I went to a parking garage disguised as an old barn about an hour west of DC in Virginia about 30 years ago to buy some air cooled VW and Porsche parts. It was sad seeing so many awesome cars sitting there but there wasn't a fleck of dust on anything. The vetting questions I was asked after getting a call back and my promise to never tell anyone what I saw and where I went is something I respect. At least they were being cared for. Now my boss at the time with his stash of 50 Corvettes is another story. That actually pissed me off.
